Towering over everything in sight, this huge wyrm appears more slender and serpentine than most other dragons. With slender neck and narrow wings, it's obvious it is far more comfortable creeping and crawling through caverns and tunnels than flying. A true creature of the Underdark, its deep, rich purple scales are so dark they almost appear black, providing near-perfect camouflage in the lightless realms below.  Its eyes do little to hide the level of cunning and patience this deep dragon has attained over the long centuries of its life

This small creature is made out of living crystalized ice. Snowflakes and small chunks of free floating ice twirl about the creature. Some of them walk on icy legs, and others float, only being half-bodies hovering over the ground. All of them appear capable of summoning chill winds and icy effects, such as a localized hailstorm, or a sudden burst of flash-frozen air, capable of freezing the very air in your lungs. Merely making contact with the creature can cause instant frostbite.

The aboleth is a revolting fishlike amphibian found primarily in subterranean lakes and rivers. An aboleth has a pink belly. Four pulsating blueblack orifices line the bottom of its body and secrete gray slime that smells like rancid grease. It uses its tail for propulsion in the water and drags itself along with its tentacles on land. An aboleth weighs about 6,500 pounds.

Aboleths speak their own language, as well as Undercommon and Aquan.
